If $${a_r} = {(\cos 2r\pi  + i\sin 2r\pi )^{1/9}}$$, <br/><br/>then the value of $$\left| {\matrix{
   {{a_1}} &amp; {{a_2}} &amp; {{a_3}}  \cr 
   {{a_4}} &amp; {{a_5}} &amp; {{a_6}}  \cr 
   {{a_7}} &amp; {{a_8}} &amp; {{a_9}}  \cr 

 } } \right|$$ is equal to

explanation:
We have,<br><br>$${a_r} = {(\cos 2r\pi  + i\sin 2r\pi )^{1/9}} = {e^{{{2\pi i} \over 9}}}$$<br><br>Now, $$\left| {\matrix{
   {{a_1}} &amp; {{a_2}} &amp; {{a_3}}  \cr 
   {{a_4}} &amp; {{a_5}} &amp; {{a_6}}  \cr 
   {{a_7}} &amp; {{a_8}} &amp; {{a_9}}  \cr 

 } } \right| = \left| {\matrix{
   {{a^{{{2\pi i} \over 9}}}} &amp; {{a^{{{4\pi i} \over 9}}}} &amp; {{a^{{{6\pi i} \over 9}}}}  \cr 
   {{a^{{{8\pi i} \over 9}}}} &amp; {{a^{{{10\pi i} \over 9}}}} &amp; {{a^{{{12\pi i} \over 9}}}}  \cr 
   {{a^{{{14\pi i} \over 9}}}} &amp; {{a^{{{16\pi i} \over 9}}}} &amp; {{a^{{{18\pi i} \over 9}}}}  \cr 

 } } \right|$$<br><br>$$ = {e^{{{2\pi i} \over 9}}} \times {e^{{{8\pi i} \over 9}}}\left| {\matrix{
   1 &amp; {{e^{{{2\pi i} \over 9}}}} &amp; {{e^{{{4\pi i} \over 9}}}}  \cr 
   1 &amp; {{e^{{{2\pi i} \over 9}}}} &amp; {{e^{{{4\pi i} \over 9}}}}  \cr 
   {{e^{{{14\pi i} \over 9}}}} &amp; {{e^{{{16\pi i} \over 9}}}} &amp; {{e^{{{18\pi i} \over 9}}}}  \cr 

 } } \right|$$<br><br>$$ = {e^{{{2\pi i} \over 9}}} \times {e^{{{8\pi i} \over 9}}} \times 0$$ ($$ \because $$ R<sub>1</sub> and R<sub>2</sub> are identical)<br><br>$$ = 0$$
